  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims to determine the effect of a supervised home-based physical fitness program
      on the aerobic capacity, quality of gait and health related quality of life in people with
      chronic ischemic stroke. Secondly, feasibility of the program for implementing a long term
      lifestyle change will be investigated.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
